Final NumPy Challenge: Student Report Analyzer
import numpy as np

marks = np.array([45, 78, 92, 35, 88, 60, 49, 100, 73, 55])
attendance = np.array([90, 85, 95, 60, 88, 70, 65, 98, 75, 80])
Print the following:
Part 1: Student Performance
Total students
Passed students (marks ≥ 50)
Failed students
Distinction students (marks ≥ 75)
Students scoring between 60 and 90 (inclusive)
Part 2: Statistics
Highest mark
Lowest mark
Average mark
Sum of all marks
Index of highest mark
Part 3: Attendance
Students with attendance ≥ 75%
Average attendance
Highest attendance
Lowest attendance
Part 4: Combined Conditions ⭐⭐⭐

Print the marks of students who:

Scored at least 60 marks
AND have attendance at least 80%

(This is one of the most useful NumPy filtering techniques.)

Part 5: Bonus ⭐⭐⭐⭐

Without using loops:

Print:

Number of students with marks above the average mark
Number of students with attendance above the average attendance




#code

import numpy as np

marks = np.array([45, 78, 92, 35, 88, 60, 49, 100, 73, 55])
attendance = np.array([90, 85, 95, 60, 88, 70, 65, 98, 75, 80])
print("Part 1:\n")
print("total students:",len(marks))
print("passed students:",marks[marks>=50])
print("failed students:",marks[marks<50])
print("Distinct students:",marks[marks>=75])
print("between 60 to 90",marks[(marks>=60) & (marks<=90)])

print("Part 2:\n")

print("highest mark:",np.max(marks))
print("lowest mark:",np.min(marks))
print("average mark:",np.mean(marks))
print("sum of all mark:",np.sum(marks))
print("index of highest rank:",np.argmax(marks))


print("Part 3:\n")

print("students with 75 percentage:",attendance[attendance>=75])
print("Average attendance:",np.mean(attendance))
print("highest attendance",np.max(attendance))
print("lowest attendance",np.min(attendance))

print("part 4:\n")

print(marks[(marks>=60) & (attendance>=80)])

print("part 5:\n")
print(len(marks[marks>np.mean(marks)]))
print(len(attendance[attendance>np.mean(attendance)]))





